WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:03.471
Previously on
Crazy Ex-Girlfriend...
Oh-oh!

00:03.504 --> 00:05.439
Whatever happened
with you and your ex?

00:05.473 --> 00:06.507
Ex?

00:10.844 --> 00:12.213
Oh, Greg, I'm sorry.

00:13.347 --> 00:15.516
Do you love her?
No.

00:16.317 --> 00:17.451
You forgive me?

00:17.485 --> 00:19.353
Of course, I forgive you, Joshy.

00:20.488 --> 00:22.256
Love doesn't work out
for me, ever.

00:22.290 --> 00:24.225
DR. AKOPIAN:
 So you are unhappy.

00:24.258 --> 00:26.327
Yeah. Duh.

00:26.360 --> 00:29.130
DR. AKOPIAN:
 Maybe it's time you see
 what else is in your life,

00:29.163 --> 00:31.132
besides Josh Chan.

00:31.165 --> 00:32.700
Oh, my gosh,
you have changed my life,

00:32.732 --> 00:35.136
Dr. Dream Ghost Akopian.

00:35.169 --> 00:36.370
You made me see past

00:36.404 --> 00:38.706
all of my delusions
that were holding me back.

00:38.739 --> 00:40.374
Josh, you don't understand?

00:40.408 --> 00:42.276
You don't see what this has

00:42.310 --> 00:44.412
all been about for Rebecca?

00:44.445 --> 00:45.546
JOSH:
 Rebecca,

00:46.414 --> 00:48.516
are you in love with me?

00:50.518 --> 00:53.287
* I was working hard
at a New York job *

00:53.321 --> 00:55.089
* Making dough
but it made me blue *

00:55.123 --> 00:56.390
* One day I was crying a lot

00:56.424 --> 00:57.625
* And so I decided to move

00:57.658 --> 00:59.460
* To West Covina, California

00:59.493 --> 01:00.628
* Brand-new pals
and new career *

01:00.661 --> 01:02.863
* It happens to be
where Josh lives *

01:02.896 --> 01:05.465
* But that's not why I'm here

01:05.498 --> 01:07.568
* She's the crazy
 ex-girlfriend *
What? No, I'm not.

01:07.601 --> 01:09.437
* She's the crazy
 ex-girlfriend *

01:09.470 --> 01:10.438
That's a sexist term.

01:10.471 --> 01:12.140
* She's the crazy
 ex-girlfriend *

01:12.173 --> 01:13.407
Can you guys stop singing
for just a second?

01:13.441 --> 01:15.676
* She's so broken inside *

01:15.709 --> 01:17.345
The situation's a lot more
nuanced than that.

01:17.378 --> 01:19.347
* C-R-A-Z-Y *

01:19.380 --> 01:20.648
Okay! We get it!

01:20.681 --> 01:23.083
* Crazy ex-girlfriend. *

01:27.388 --> 01:29.357
Why do you have
all these photos?

01:29.390 --> 01:32.193
Yep, okay,
so here's what happened.

01:32.226 --> 01:36.697
I had... have...

01:36.730 --> 01:39.533
...had feelings for you,
indeed, yes.

01:39.567 --> 01:43.437
God, this is awkward, um,

01:43.471 --> 01:46.240
I came here to tell you
that Valencia...

01:46.274 --> 01:47.541
Valencia and you
are staying together.

01:47.575 --> 01:48.342
No-- I-I-I I gathered.
Yeah.

01:48.376 --> 01:49.910
I get it and that
makes sense, yeah.

01:49.943 --> 01:52.846
Josh, I'm actually
very glad you're here,

01:52.880 --> 01:56.550
because, um, I realized
some things on my recent trip.

01:56.584 --> 01:58.386
And, um, one of
the things I realized

01:58.419 --> 01:59.920
is that I need
to break my old patterns.

01:59.953 --> 02:01.689
Okay.

02:01.722 --> 02:03.491
Yes, uh, starting with...

02:03.524 --> 02:08.562
(sighs) I've been horrible to
Valencia, like, really horrible,

02:08.596 --> 02:11.199
and I really want
to reach out to her.

02:11.232 --> 02:13.434
I really wouldn't.
I really
think I should.

02:13.467 --> 02:16.504
She really hates your guts.
Understandable,

02:16.537 --> 02:19.440
and I will just
have to transcend that.

02:21.575 --> 02:26.280
I am trying to break free of
anything unhealthy or damaging.

02:27.681 --> 02:31.385
So, um, that starts with,
uh, trashing these.

02:32.620 --> 02:33.354
Unless you want them.

02:33.387 --> 02:35.956
(both laugh)
No, no, that's okay.

02:35.989 --> 02:37.558
Yeah.
Yeah.

02:37.591 --> 02:40.594
Although, um, you know,
some of those are great angles

02:40.628 --> 02:43.464
that you can't get with
a selfie, so, uh...

02:43.497 --> 02:45.433
Sure, yeah, yes.
Yeah.

02:45.466 --> 02:46.567
Thanks.

02:46.600 --> 02:47.868
Okay, well, there it is.

02:47.901 --> 02:49.470
That's the last
of the Josh Chan stuff.

02:49.503 --> 02:51.339
There was stuff?

02:51.372 --> 02:52.540
No.

02:54.675 --> 02:56.744
Well, I guess I should go.

02:56.777 --> 02:58.479
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Of course, get out.

02:58.512 --> 03:01.649
Get out of here.
(laughs)
Yeah, yeah.

03:01.682 --> 03:03.684
Bye, Josh.

03:10.891 --> 03:12.660
(sighing)

03:22.002 --> 03:23.671
Can I get another beer?
I'm trying to study.

03:23.704 --> 03:27.675
Studying and drinking
at the same time: good decision.

03:27.708 --> 03:29.277
I know, right?

03:29.310 --> 03:31.679
It's easy.
It's extension school.

03:31.712 --> 03:34.282
I-I don't like to tell
a lot of people this,

03:34.315 --> 03:36.016
but I got into
Emory business school.

03:36.049 --> 03:37.518
It's a pretty good school.

03:37.551 --> 03:39.553
They call it like
the Harvard of the South.

03:39.587 --> 03:41.522
I thought the Harvard
of the South was Vanderbilt.

03:41.555 --> 03:44.958
No. No. No.

03:44.992 --> 03:49.697
Yeah, so I got into school,
and then my dad got sick,

03:49.730 --> 03:52.466
so now I'm working my way
through school here.

03:52.500 --> 03:54.668
You know? I can't be slinging

03:54.702 --> 03:57.971
drinks to losers until
I'm like 60 years old.

03:59.006 --> 04:00.808
(scoffs)

04:02.776 --> 04:06.680
Oh, boy, look at this.
Just what I need.

04:08.749 --> 04:11.552
Hi.
Hey.

04:11.585 --> 04:13.621
I thought you drank
at Home Base.

04:13.654 --> 04:18.625
I drink anywhere,
but I do my study-drinking here.

04:18.659 --> 04:19.726
Got it.

04:19.760 --> 04:20.961
Can I pull up a
stool next to you,

04:20.994 --> 04:22.563
or do you want to be alone?

04:22.596 --> 04:24.565
I could go home and
drink some mouthwash.

04:24.598 --> 04:25.766
Mouthwash, wow.

04:25.799 --> 04:27.635
That's almost as sad
as a girl coming to

04:27.668 --> 04:29.637
a strange bar by herself.

04:29.670 --> 04:32.606
Sad says the man
with an open textbook

04:32.640 --> 04:34.975
next to an open container.

04:35.008 --> 04:36.877
This is fun. I like this.

04:36.910 --> 04:39.513
Do you want to hang out for
a while and insult each other?

04:39.547 --> 04:41.615
Ah, what would your girlfriend
think about that?

04:41.649 --> 04:44.685
Um, Heather?
Uh, yeah, no, we're donezo.

04:44.718 --> 04:45.719
(blows raspberry)

04:45.753 --> 04:47.755
Oh, wow. I had no idea.

04:47.788 --> 04:49.590
Can I get you a drink?

04:49.623 --> 04:51.759
Nothing goes better with a
fine lager than a little snark.

04:51.792 --> 04:53.461
Wait. Go back to
the Heather thing.

04:53.494 --> 04:54.828
Are you okay?
Let's-let-let's talk.

04:54.862 --> 04:58.532
Talk is not on the bar menu,

04:58.566 --> 04:59.633
but we could ask.

04:59.667 --> 05:01.769
Okay, so, yeah,
here's the thing.

05:01.802 --> 05:04.438
Old me would have
been totally down

05:04.472 --> 05:06.707
for, like, an
old-fashioned barb fest,

05:06.740 --> 05:08.342
but I've decided recently

05:08.376 --> 05:10.744
that I'm trying to
change my patterns.

05:12.112 --> 05:15.082
So I'm gonna go.

05:15.115 --> 05:17.017
No, come on. Come on.

05:17.050 --> 05:18.419
I'm a glutton for punishment.

05:18.452 --> 05:19.620
Stay.

05:19.653 --> 05:20.654
Let's do this.

05:20.688 --> 05:22.089
We can make bad
decisions together.

05:22.122 --> 05:24.692
We could run in traffic.

05:26.827 --> 05:28.028
No? Okay.

05:28.061 --> 05:30.731
Boy, she really digs you.

05:30.764 --> 05:31.999
She's in love with someone else,

05:32.032 --> 05:34.668
but I figure ten, 11 years
of me trying,

05:34.702 --> 05:35.969
I'm a lock.

05:42.810 --> 05:44.878
Okay, what is happening?

05:44.912 --> 05:46.747
Why are you throwing out
all this Josh stuff?

05:46.780 --> 05:48.616
I told you, I've gone
cold turkey on the Chan.

05:48.649 --> 05:51.485
I'm done. It's not good for me,
and you know that.

05:51.519 --> 05:54.422
D-- oh, G-- you have
to keep the macaroni portrait.

05:54.455 --> 05:55.723
That took two weeks.

05:55.756 --> 05:57.758
No, no, Paula, I'm breaking
my old patterns.

05:57.791 --> 05:59.760
Break old pat-- I--
what does that even mean?

05:59.793 --> 06:01.695
Did you go to a
bumper sticker store?

06:01.729 --> 06:04.798
No, I just realized a lot of
things on my trip to New York,

06:04.832 --> 06:07.167
while I was in a
bumper sticker store.

06:07.200 --> 06:09.136
Okay, but you're right
about this, actually,

06:09.169 --> 06:10.938
it has a lot of dry goods on it,

06:10.971 --> 06:12.139
it actually could be useful
for my earthquake kit,

06:12.172 --> 06:13.707
so I will keep this.
That's my girl.

06:13.741 --> 06:15.476
But everything else
goes in the trash.

06:15.509 --> 06:17.711
Hmm, hmm.
Oh, come on.

06:17.745 --> 06:20.848
(gasps)
Not Channy bear. I forbid it.

06:22.883 --> 06:24.117
Fine, maybe I'll just
put Channy bear

06:24.151 --> 06:27.988
on a high shelf in case
of a bearmergency.

06:28.021 --> 06:30.724
But the rest of
this is going, bye.

06:30.758 --> 06:31.725
Oh, come on...
Bye, letters to Josh.

06:31.759 --> 06:32.960
First drafts,
second drafts.

06:32.993 --> 06:34.161
In the trash.
No.

06:34.194 --> 06:35.429
Yep.
That's...

06:35.463 --> 06:36.864
That's insanity.
Nope. Nope.

06:36.897 --> 06:37.731
Good-bye, Josh thong

06:37.765 --> 06:38.999
that I never wo--
I don't wear thongs.

06:39.032 --> 06:40.033
Why did I even get this?

06:40.067 --> 06:41.869
You have finally lost it.

06:41.902 --> 06:43.837
You have left the reservation
and I-I can't... I'm not...

06:43.871 --> 06:45.005
I can't watch it.
I don't care.
I don't care.

06:45.038 --> 06:46.874
I'm not supporting this.
No, uh-uh.

06:58.919 --> 07:02.723
Hey... I'm so nervous,
aren't you?

07:02.756 --> 07:04.625
That last test...
(groans)

07:04.658 --> 07:06.694
Was pretty easy,
at least for me.

07:06.727 --> 07:08.629
Wow, that's impressive.

07:08.662 --> 07:10.163
You must be smart.

07:10.197 --> 07:11.865
Yeah, well.

07:11.899 --> 07:14.468
I-I don't like to tell
people this, but, um...

07:14.502 --> 07:16.504
Oh, you don't have to tell me
something you don't like to...

07:16.537 --> 07:18.105
I got into the
Harvard of the South.

07:18.138 --> 07:20.774
Emory? You know it?

07:20.808 --> 07:21.809
Emory?

07:21.842 --> 07:23.176
The Harvard of the South
is Duke.

07:23.210 --> 07:26.747
No. No, no.
Emory. Google it.

07:26.780 --> 07:28.816
PROFESSOR:
So, everyone,

07:28.849 --> 07:31.852
overall there were
some nice efforts,

07:31.885 --> 07:36.189
but, uh, some of you,
I'm sad to say, fell short.

07:43.597 --> 07:45.766
I'm really not sure
what rubric you're using

07:45.799 --> 07:47.801
to grade these, but...

07:47.835 --> 07:49.202
Doesn't take much
of a rubric to see

07:49.236 --> 07:50.838
that you didn't put in
much of an effort here.

07:50.871 --> 07:53.841
Oh, well, you know,
I work full-time.

07:53.874 --> 07:54.708
My dad is sick.

07:54.742 --> 07:57.545
I work two jobs
and my husband is dead.

07:57.578 --> 08:00.180
I am very sorry to hear that,

08:00.213 --> 08:02.716
but I was not involved.

08:02.750 --> 08:04.852
Your next assignment
is an essay due Friday.

08:04.885 --> 08:06.887
You can do better,
Mr. Serrano.

08:06.920 --> 08:09.022
You got into the
Harvard of the South, after all,

08:09.056 --> 08:12.626
which you somehow managed
to mention on your test.

08:12.660 --> 08:14.762
A multiple choice test.

08:14.795 --> 08:16.797
So, you're busting my balls

08:16.830 --> 08:19.199
about an intro class
at an extension school?

08:19.232 --> 08:20.968
Cool, yeah. Makes sense.

08:21.001 --> 08:24.905
Look, I don't know you very
well, but from where I stand,

08:24.938 --> 08:27.975
it seems like you've made the
choice not to try or something.

08:28.008 --> 08:30.210
Oh, please, don't you
worry about my decisions.

08:30.243 --> 08:33.847
I will decide
about my decisions.

08:38.085 --> 08:41.054
(mocking the teacher):
Choosing not to try, Greg.

08:41.087 --> 08:43.256
You got into Emory, Greg.

08:43.289 --> 08:45.092
I mean, duh,
I could have done better.

08:45.125 --> 08:47.828
I could have gotten an "A"
on that test if I'd wanted to.

08:48.862 --> 08:50.598
* Whoop-de-frickin'-do, an "A"

08:50.631 --> 08:53.066
* What's an "A"?
It's just a letter on a page *

08:53.100 --> 08:55.235
* Meant to distract us
from the pain *

08:55.268 --> 08:58.005
* But it's not like any "A" can
make a difference in the day *

08:58.038 --> 08:59.840
* Sure, I could get an "A"
if I wanted to get an "A" *

08:59.873 --> 09:01.008
* But who cares about an "A"?

09:01.041 --> 09:02.776
* I don't

09:02.810 --> 09:04.311
* I don't care

09:04.344 --> 09:05.579
* Although I could
have made that grade *

09:05.613 --> 09:06.747
* If I did care

09:06.780 --> 09:10.217
* But I don't

09:10.250 --> 09:12.720
* But I could if I wanted to

09:12.753 --> 09:14.622
* Whoop-de-frickin'-do

09:14.655 --> 09:17.190
* Look at this guy in the red
and blue striped tie *

09:17.224 --> 09:18.926
* Making millions till he dies

09:18.959 --> 09:21.629
* Selling bonds and stocks
to other guys in ties *

09:21.662 --> 09:23.631
* Who have millions
with which to buy *

09:23.664 --> 09:24.865
* A bunch of bonds
and stocks and ties *

09:24.898 --> 09:26.166
* I'd rather die

09:26.199 --> 09:27.635
* Which I will eventually,
of course *

09:27.668 --> 09:29.336
* But in the meantime

09:29.369 --> 09:32.606
* I could make millions selling
stocks and bonds and ties *

09:32.640 --> 09:34.041
* If I tried

09:34.074 --> 09:35.375
* But I don't

09:35.408 --> 09:39.647
* But I could, but I don't

09:39.680 --> 09:43.050
* But I could if I wanted to

09:43.083 --> 09:45.719
* Yeah

09:45.753 --> 09:48.388
* Yeah, I could if I wanted to

09:48.421 --> 09:52.059
* Who cares?

09:52.092 --> 09:54.762
* Whoop-de-frickin'-do

09:54.795 --> 09:56.063
* A happy dad

09:56.096 --> 09:57.197
* With his big dad calves

09:57.230 --> 09:58.766
* And his stupid baseball cap

09:58.799 --> 09:59.967
* And his T-ball shirt

10:00.000 --> 10:02.002
* And dumb-ass son
throwing a ball *

10:02.035 --> 10:04.672
* Like it's so important
to know how to throw a ball *

10:04.705 --> 10:06.073
* Whoop-de-frickin'-do

10:06.106 --> 10:07.641
* Who cares about
throwing a ball *

10:07.675 --> 10:08.942
* Or having a kid

10:08.976 --> 10:10.277
* It'll get you
nowhere in life *

10:10.310 --> 10:12.212
* Not like getting
anywhere matters *

10:12.245 --> 10:14.982
* Although I guess it does
if you care *

10:15.015 --> 10:18.085
* Which I don't

10:18.118 --> 10:20.921
* But I could, but I don't

10:20.954 --> 10:23.390
* But I could if I wanted to

10:23.423 --> 10:26.059
* Yeah

10:26.093 --> 10:29.396
* Whoop-de-frickin'-do
if I wanted to *

10:29.429 --> 10:32.232
* This song sucks

10:32.265 --> 10:35.402
* I could make it good
if I wanted to *

10:35.435 --> 10:38.338
* Yeah

10:38.371 --> 10:41.975
* Yeah, I could
if I wanted to. *

10:45.913 --> 10:48.181
I could do that
if I wanted to.

10:48.215 --> 10:51.218
You're an idiot.

10:53.386 --> 10:55.022
(sighs)

10:55.055 --> 10:57.024
Oh, my God, this is nuts.

10:57.057 --> 10:58.859
Okay, you can't give up
on Josh right now.

10:58.892 --> 11:00.193
You are so close.

11:00.227 --> 11:03.063
Paula, he picked Valencia.

11:03.096 --> 11:04.031
Like, in front of my face.

11:04.064 --> 11:05.966
Game over.

11:05.999 --> 11:07.034
What? No.

11:07.067 --> 11:09.069
Game has just begun.

11:09.102 --> 11:11.338
Okay, you have antibodies
to his saliva.

11:11.371 --> 11:13.807
You cannot give up.
You have traction.

11:13.841 --> 11:15.809
He-he touched the side
of your boob, I saw it.

11:15.843 --> 11:17.444
(doorbell rings)

11:17.477 --> 11:20.213
Can you get whoever that...
Yeah, I will get that.

11:20.247 --> 11:23.383
And... just... let's continue
the convo later, okay?

11:23.416 --> 11:25.819
And if it's the people across
the street from that church,

11:25.853 --> 11:27.821
just tell them I don't believe
and will never believe.

11:27.855 --> 11:29.389
Rebecca.

11:31.124 --> 11:33.794
Hello, everyone
in Josh's family.

11:33.827 --> 11:35.462
Hi.
Oh, my gosh.

11:35.495 --> 11:38.832
I haven't seen you since
the last book club.

11:38.866 --> 11:40.233
(squeals)
I haven't seen you got engaged.

11:40.267 --> 11:41.835
How does it feel?

11:41.869 --> 11:43.136
It feels like I've
been waiting seven years

11:43.170 --> 11:45.438
for Phillip to propose,
because I have.

11:45.472 --> 11:46.807
(laughing)

11:46.840 --> 11:47.941
Let me see the rock.

11:47.975 --> 11:49.076
Oh, my gosh, I mean,

11:49.109 --> 11:51.078
Phillip said he was going
for it, but... (whistles)

11:51.111 --> 11:52.846
He said you were
so helpful getting it.

11:52.880 --> 11:54.014
Oh, it was no problem at all.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.315
I helped my client, Moshe,

11:55.348 --> 11:56.850
through a very complicated
subdivision deal,

11:56.884 --> 11:58.151
and he said he could hook me up

11:58.185 --> 11:59.920
with non-blood diamonds
at a discount.

11:59.953 --> 12:02.155
And never pass up
a good discount, right?

12:02.189 --> 12:04.124
I know what you're thinking--
like, diamonds, discounts,

12:04.157 --> 12:06.493
those are some like classic
Jew moves, you know?

12:08.095 --> 12:09.930
What are you doing here?

12:09.963 --> 12:12.399
Jayma has something to ask you.

12:12.432 --> 12:15.368
Look, I know that
this is sudden,

12:15.402 --> 12:18.238
and we haven't known
each other that long--

12:18.271 --> 12:20.540
God, I feel like I'm
proposing or something.

12:20.573 --> 12:23.343
You've been such
a good friend to the family.

12:23.376 --> 12:25.212
You wrote Jastenity that letter
to get into Harvard.

12:25.245 --> 12:29.149
Unfortunately the letter
was better than her application,

12:29.182 --> 12:30.918
but she did get
into Cal State Northridge,

12:30.951 --> 12:32.886
which is the
Harvard of Northridge.

12:32.920 --> 12:34.021
Yeah, it is.

12:34.054 --> 12:35.222
There we go.

12:35.255 --> 12:36.556
Anyway, what I'm
trying to say is,

12:36.589 --> 12:40.060
how would you like to be
a bridesmaid at my wedding?

12:42.229 --> 12:43.797
PAULA:
You mean,

12:43.831 --> 12:44.898
be an official part
of the Chan fam-bam?

12:44.932 --> 12:46.166
She'd love to.

12:47.234 --> 12:51.171
You want me to be
a bridesmaid.

12:51.204 --> 12:54.207
Aw, you're such a lovely girl,
Rebecca.

12:54.241 --> 12:56.543
We would be so honored
if you would

12:56.576 --> 12:58.345
